{"article_id":"iWw2XkkYr5jFr6Be","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Kim , Moon Pledge Denuclearization Of Peninsula And End To Korean War","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Following a historic meeting between North Korea 's Kim Jong Un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"the leaders appeared side by side","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to make an extraordinary announcement :","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The two nations","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"- technically in a state of war for more than six decades -","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"would work toward a permanent peace treaty and the elimination of nuclear weapons from the peninsula .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"`` I am very proud to say","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"that I pay tribute to the bold and courageous decision","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"taken by Chairman Kim , ''","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"Moon said ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"the two sides had agreed to a peace treaty and the `` complete denuclearization '' of the Korean Peninsula .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"`` We have long hoped for this moment to arrive , ''","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Kim ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"standing next to Moon ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"said .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"`` We are not people","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"who should be confronting each other , ''","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"the North Korean leader said .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"`` We should be living in unity . ''","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"While the agreement contains lofty language ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"it will be up to diplomats , bureaucrats and militaries on both sides to work through specific steps","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"to reach those goals .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"And the effort will require detailed negotiation between both Koreas and the United States ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"which could take months , if not years ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"to conclude .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"For now , the agreement mentions denuclearization","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"but does n't offer specific steps ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"which will lead to a lot of skepticism","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"about how committed the North is","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"given its past abandonment of denuclearization agreements .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"The day began with a handshake","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"that symbolized hope","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"that two Koreas could create a lasting rapprochement .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Kim ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"flanked by bodyguards in matching black suits ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"stepped out of a building on the northern side of the village of Panmunjom ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"where the two sides ended the Korean War in 1953 with a simple truce , but no broader peace treaty .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Notably absent in this shared security zone were the dozens of armed soldiers","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"who typically stand guard near the military demarcation line .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Two previous summits , in 2000 and 2007 , were unable to make progress on the most pressing issue","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"- the North 's pursuit of nuclear weapons .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"The nuclear question looms even larger this time around","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"- in the past year , Pyongyang has not only demonstrated its ability","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"to produce such weapons","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"but also the potential","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"to deliver them via long-range ballistic missiles","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that can reach as far as the continental United States .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"The Blue House , South Korea 's presidential residence , said","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"the two leaders had a `` frank discussion '' in a morning session ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"which included the subject of denuclearization .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"A year of especially serious tensions","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"leading up to Friday","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"was followed by a sudden thaw and an offer by Kim in recent weeks","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"to meet with President Trump .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Mere months ago , the two leaders were trading insults","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"and threatening to wage war .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"However , the White House appears to be taking Kim 's offer seriously","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"and the two men could meet as soon as next month .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Moon , on the south side of the border , walked over","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"to meet Kim","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"so that their handshake could be photographed at the symbolic military demarcation line","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"that divides the North from South .","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"In the meticulously choreographed ceremony , hands clasped","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"and Moon invited Kim over an ankle-high concrete barrier","depth":17},{"id":66,"text":"that divides the two countries","depth":17},{"id":67,"text":"- the first time","depth":17},{"id":68,"text":"the North Korean leader","depth":19},{"id":69,"text":"- or any North Korean leader -","depth":19},{"id":70,"text":"had ever set foot in the South .","depth":18},{"id":71,"text":"Then Kim gestured to Moon","depth":17},{"id":72,"text":"to take a step into the North ,","depth":17},{"id":73,"text":"which the South Korean leader did .","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"The presidential office later said","depth":16},{"id":75,"text":"that the unscripted moment came","depth":17},{"id":76,"text":"after Moon said","depth":18},{"id":77,"text":"he wanted to visit North Korea someday .","depth":18},{"id":78,"text":"Kim reacted quickly","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"by offering to have him step right over to the northern side for a few moments ,","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"before they crossed back over to the South , hand in hand .","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"They walked side by side down a red carpet ,","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"observed a brightly-colored traditional Korean honor guard ceremony ,","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"before proceeding into the three-story Peace House for their summit .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"Entering the Peace House ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"Kim wrote in the guest book :","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"`` New history starts from now , at the historic starting point of an era of peace . ''","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"The pair posed for photos in front of a picture of North Korea 's Mount Geumgangsan ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"which has special significance for all Koreans","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"dating to before the Middle Ages .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Kim Yong Chol , the head of North Korea 's national intelligence service , began clapping","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"and others from both sides joined in .","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"`` It feels embarrassing to be applauded","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"just for shaking hands , ''","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"the North Korean leader said ,","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"but acknowledged ,","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"`` The norms are changing . ''","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"`` Did that make for a good picture ? ''","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"he asked","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"as journalists and others laughed .","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"Once seated inside ,","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"Kim quipped","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"that he brought Pyongyang 's famous naengmyeon , cold noodles , `` from far away , ''","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"then corrected himself","depth":15},{"id":104,"text":"to say","depth":16},{"id":105,"text":"it was n't so far away at all .","depth":16},{"id":106,"text":"The two leaders and their wives were expected to attend a dinner banquet Friday evening ,","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"featuring the noodles","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"brought from the North .","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"Even with the outward appearance of geniality , however , lingering suspicions were evident :","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"After Moon stepped out of Peace House ,","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"two North Korean security guards swept into the lobby ,","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"sprayed the chair at the guestbook signing desk with sanitizer","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"and wiped it down .","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"They also cleaned the guestbook and pen with sanitizer - twice .","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"Then the guards used electronic gear","depth":16},{"id":116,"text":"to scan the chair and signing desk .","depth":16},{"id":117,"text":"The reason ?","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"A South Korean security guard told reporters","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"that their North Korean counterparts were checking for explosives and recording devices .","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"After separate lunches , the two leaders commemorated the summit","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"by shoveling soil around a pine tree","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"and then sprinkling it with water from South Korea 's Han River and North Korea 's Taedong River .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"Moon and Kim then walked away from the cameras and microphones","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"and sat at a bench","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"to have a conversation","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"without their aides .","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"For much of that lengthy discussion , Kim could be seen","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"listening intently to Moon ,","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"smiling","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"and laughing at times .","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"NPR news assistant Se Eun Gong contributed to this story from Ilsan , South Korea .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":263,"left":0,"right":262,"relation":"organiza